  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare the effectiveness of combined antibiotic ophthalmic solution (neomycin sulfate,
      polymyxin B sulfate and gramicidin) with placebo (artificial tear) in the treatment of
      hordeolum after incision and curettage
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Hordeolum is a common eyelid disease. In case of mass, I&amp;C is required but role of antibiotic
      after I&amp;C is not clear. It may not need in post drainage period.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
